  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Demo in  sharepoint : https://sites.inside-share3.bosch.com/sites/167912/Documents/0000.Overall%20Project/16.%20Functional%20Safety/10_Supporting_Workproducts/03_Safety_Mechanisms/SM53%20Safe%20Telltale/_build/html/swrs/swrs_index.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Document is like below :"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-5-16_17-55-35.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-5-16_17-55-35.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "HOW TO :"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "1 Install  sphinx with python or  use sphinx  docker image(sphinxdoc/sphinx:latest) ."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Generate docs with docker could refer below steps, Otherwise could install sphinx with python Documenting with Sphinx"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Demo docker-compose.yml   :",
        "Install below sphinx extensions after first step:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "pip install sphinx     （Version: 7.3.7）",
        "pip install pillow        （Version: 10.3.0）",
        "pip install sphinxcontrib-plantuml   （Version: 0.30）",
        "pip install sphinx-rtd-theme               （Version: 2.0.0）",
        "pip install sphinx_needs  （Version: 2.1.0）",
        "pip install breathe             （Version: 4.35.0）",
        "pip install doxysphinx         （Version: 3.3.8）"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "2   For CNCovbase, we have template sphinx config file"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "convbase.zip"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3 Generate SWCDD html"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "cd ./convbase",
        "sphinx-build -b html source build",
        "we will get html document in ./build folder"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-4-28_15-57-49.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-4-28_15-57-49.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Congratulations!  You got a html document as below:"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-4-28_16-2-26.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-4-28_16-2-26.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Taiji Practice"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Template repo : project:projects/taiji/cnconv/config/FuSa/swcdd · Gerrit Code Review (bosch.com)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Refer to template folder to generate swcdd and uds at one time."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In every SM's sphinx subfolder :"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "mkdir build &&  cd build",
        "cmake ..",
        "make sphinx"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "1). add comments like this"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-5-13_13-48-40.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-5-13_13-48-40.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "2). If \\implement or \\verify   is used in before project,  need update  uds/requirements.md which is supposed to generate UDS Req chapter like below :"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-5-13_13-53-12.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-5-13_13-53-12.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "3). In Taiji platform we could use DOORS ID attribute in DNG to track requirement id in code and classic Doors."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-5-14_19-41-57.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-5-14_19-41-57.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "4). We could save DNG page as html file, so we can extract requirement id link via script. It looks like below ."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Sphinx%20%20generate%20SWRS/SWCDD/UDS/image-2024-5-17_11-39-18.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Sphinx  generate SWRS_SWCDD_UDS/image-2024-5-17_11-39-18.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
